    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1864-10-05T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1864-10-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="518"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d518">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Burnley</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1864-10-05">
                            <hi rend="italic">October</hi> 5, 1864.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of
                    your communication of the 3d instant, in regard to the seizure of the British
                    sloop Racer by the United States schooner Hope, and preferring a claim to
                    compensation on account of losses growing out of the capture and detention of
                    the Racer.</p>
                <p>In reply, I have the honor to inform you that I have submitted the case to the
                    Secretary of the Navy, with a view to investigation and proper proceedings.</p>
                <p>I have the honor to be, sir, with the highest consideration, your obedient
                    servant.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">J. Hume Burnley,</hi> esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c.,
                            &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
